description.p:
Exemplary methods for the production of pH responsive latexes, preferably the above described HASE systems, include the steps of:
(i) preparing a reaction mixture by combining an aqueous solvent containing at least one stabilizer, preferably at least one surfactant, and a monomer mixture as defined above;
(ii) homogenizing said reaction mixture of step (i) to generate stabilized miniemulsion droplets containing the monomer mixture;
(iii) adding a polymerization initiator, preferably a water-soluble polymerization initiator, to polymerize the miniemulsion droplets.

claim.claim-text:
The water-based polymer system of any one of claims 1 to 13, wherein
a. the polymer system has a HWSP content of 5 to 55 wt.-%, preferably 10 to 50 wt.-%, more preferably 15 to 50 wt.-%, relative to the polymer system;
b. the polymer system has a water content of 60 to 100 wt.-%, preferably 70 to 90 wt.-% relative to the total weight of the liquid phase of the polymer system.
